Read first time January 14, 2025
Committee: Revenue
1 THE MEMBERS OF THE ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA, FIRST
2 SESSION, RESOLVE THAT:
3 Section 1. At the general election in November 2026, the following
4 proposed amendment to the Constitution of Nebraska shall be submitted to
5 the electors of the State of Nebraska for approval or rejection:
6 To add a new section 1C to Article VIII:
7 VIII-1C The state and any political subdivision thereof shall be
8 prohibited from levying an inheritance tax.
9 Sec. 2. The proposed amendment shall be submitted to the electors
10 in the manner prescribed by the Constitution of Nebraska, Article XVI,
11 section 1, with the following ballot language:
12 A constitutional amendment to prohibit the levying of an inheritance
13 tax by the state or any political subdivision thereof.
14 For
15 Against.
